<subSubSection id="C363652FFF8EBE44FF27703DF59FF8F4" pageId="106" pageNumber="693" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC636A4FF8EBE44FF27703DF519F94C" blockId="106.[210,1444,1618,1816]" pageId="106" pageNumber="693">
DIAGNOSIS. — 
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8EBE44FE88703CF503F989" box="[379,554,1619,1642]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="693">Shell morphology</emphasis>
. Shell external, solid, oval, with only 1 whorl visible. Aperture longitudinal, as long as the shell, anteriorly rounded. Columella thickened, in some cases with a vestigial callus near the posterior end of the aperture. Operculum absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC636A4FF8EBE44FF0170D5F59FF8F4" blockId="106.[210,1444,1618,1816]" pageId="106" pageNumber="693">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8EBE44FF0170D5F662F932" box="[242,331,1722,1745]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="693">Anatomy</emphasis>
. Large headshield, with a deep medial slit separating the shield into 2 posteriorly projecting lobes. Parapodia short, covering the laterals of the shell. Radula composed of denticulate rachidian teeth and a triangular lateral tooth on each side. Reproductive system unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363652FFF8FBE45FF017765F5A9FDF7" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC636A4FF8FBE45FF017765F5D3FE69" blockId="107.[242,1475,266,533]" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">
REMARKS. — 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FE747764F6F2FEC1" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1847" box="[391,475,267,290]" class="Gastropoda" family="Alacuppidae" genus="Roxania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FE747764F6F2FEC1" box="[391,475,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Roxania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by Leach (1847) for the single species 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FBDE7764F3D6FEC1" authority="Leach" authorityName="Leach" box="[1069,1279,266,290]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bullidae" genus="Bulla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cranchii">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FBDE7764F391FEC1" box="[1069,1208,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Bulla cranchii</emphasis>
Leach
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FAF57764F233FEC1" box="[1286,1306,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">in</emphasis>
Fleming, 1828. Subsequently Dall (1896) described the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FCD57741F4B7FEA6" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1896" box="[806,926,302,325]" class="Gastropoda" family="Scaphandridae" genus="Abderospira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FCD57741F4B7FEA6" box="[806,926,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Abderospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a fossil species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FB897741F64AFE84" authority="Dall, 1896" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1896" class="Gastropoda" family="Aplustridae" genus="Bullina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="chipolana" subGenus="Abderospira">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FB897741F3EDFEA6" box="[1146,1220,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Bullina</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FB257741F267FEA6" box="[1238,1358,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Abderospira</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FA937741F2EBFEA6" box="[1376,1474,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">chipolana</emphasis>
Dall, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, from the Tertiary of 
<collectingRegion id="49BDF846FF8FBE45FDBA7720F5B1FE84" box="[585,664,335,359]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Florida</collectingRegion>
. The shell characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FC34773EF316FE8B" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1896" box="[967,1087,337,360]" class="Gastropoda" family="Scaphandridae" genus="Abderospira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FC34773EF316FE8B" box="[967,1087,337,360]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Abderospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FA9D773FF2EBFE84" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1847" box="[1390,1474,336,359]" class="Gastropoda" family="Alacuppidae" genus="Roxania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FA9D773FF2EBFE84" box="[1390,1474,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Roxania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the names have been regarded as synonyms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC636A4FF8FBE45FEE377FAF5A9FDF7" blockId="107.[242,1475,266,533]" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">
Iredale (1918) considered that 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FDA477FAF582FE4F" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1847" box="[599,683,405,428]" class="Gastropoda" family="Alacuppidae" genus="Roxania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FDA477FAF582FE4F" box="[599,683,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Roxania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FC7B77FAF354FE4E" authority="Stephens, 1834" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1834" box="[904,1149,405,429]" class="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" family="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Roxana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FC7B77FAF4FCFE4F" box="[904,981,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Roxana</emphasis>
Stephens, 1834
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FB7977FAF238FE4E" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1162,1297,405,429]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
) and introduced the replacement name 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FE1477D6F5D9FE2C" authority="Iredale, 1918" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1918" box="[487,752,439,464]" class="Gastropoda" family="Scaphandridae" genus="Damoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FE1477D6F574FE33" box="[487,605,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Damoniella</emphasis>
Iredale, 1918
</taxonomicName>
. According to the 
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FC4077D6F4CCFE33" box="[947,997,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Code</emphasis>
(ICZN 1999: Article 56.2), even if the difference between two genus-group names is only one letter, they are not homonyms. Therefore 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D27FF8FBE45FB4E77B4F2EBFE11" authority="Iredale, 1918" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1918" box="[1213,1474,474,498]" class="Gastropoda" family="Scaphandridae" genus="Damoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="107" pageNumber="694" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB6FF8FBE45FB4E77B4F21AFE11" box="[1213,1331,475,498]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="694">Damoniella</emphasis>
Iredale, 1918
</taxonomicName>
is an unnecessary replacement name.
</paragraph>
